# Animation & Transition Patterns

Reference file for the frontend improvement agent. When fixing **P2 — UX & Interaction Quality** motion issues, follow these patterns exactly.

---

## 1. TOKEN REFERENCE

These are defined in `web-ui-engineering-bar.mdc` §7. Use them by name — never hardcode values.

```css
/* Easing */
--ease-default:   cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);     /* Most UI transitions */
--ease-in:        cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1);          /* Elements exiting */
--ease-out:       cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1);          /* Elements entering */
--ease-in-out:    cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);        /* Balanced */
--ease-bounce:    cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);  /* Playful, sparingly */

/* Duration */
--duration-instant:  50ms;   /* Hover color change */
--duration-fast:     100ms;  /* Button press */
--duration-normal:   150ms;  /* Most transitions */
--duration-moderate: 250ms;  /* Dropdowns, menus */
--duration-slow:     350ms;  /* Modals, drawers */
--duration-slower:   500ms;  /* Page transitions only */
```

---

## 2. GLOBAL KEYFRAMES

Define these once at the application root. All transition components reference them.

```css
/* Enter: fade + slide up */
@keyframes fadeSlideIn {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(8px);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}

/* Enter: fade only */
@keyframes fadeIn {
  from { opacity: 0; }
  to   { opacity: 1; }
}

/* Enter: scale up (for modals, popovers) */
@keyframes scaleIn {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: scale(0.96);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1);
  }
}

/* Exit: fade out */
@keyframes fadeOut {
  from { opacity: 1; }
  to   { opacity: 0; }
}

/* Exit: fade + slide down */
@keyframes fadeSlideOut {
  from {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(8px);
  }
}

/* Reduced motion: no movement, opacity only */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  @keyframes fadeSlideIn {
    from { opacity: 0; }
    to   { opacity: 1; }
  }
  @keyframes scaleIn {
    from { opacity: 0; }
    to   { opacity: 1; }
  }
  @keyframes fadeSlideOut {
    from { opacity: 1; }
    to   { opacity: 0; }
  }
}
```

---

## 3. FADE-IN WRAPPER COMPONENT

The most-used transition. Wraps any async content that appears after loading.

```tsx
import { type ReactNode, type CSSProperties } from 'react';

interface FadeInProps {
  children: ReactNode;
  duration?: string;
  delay?: string;
  className?: string;
  style?: CSSProperties;
}

function FadeIn({
  children,
  duration = '200ms',
  delay = '0ms',
  className,
  style,
}: FadeInProps) {
  return (
    <div
      className={className}
      style={{
        animation: `fadeSlideIn ${duration} var(--ease-out) ${delay} both`,
        ...style,
      }}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Usage:**
```tsx
// Simple — async content that just appeared
<FadeIn>
  <UserProfile user={data} />
</FadeIn>

// With delay — second item in a sequence
<FadeIn delay="80ms">
  <ActivityFeed items={activities} />
</FadeIn>
```

