## 6. DROPDOWN / MENU TRANSITIONS

```css
.dropdown-enter {
  animation: fadeSlideIn var(--duration-moderate) var(--ease-out) both;
}

.dropdown-exit {
  animation: fadeSlideOut var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-in) both;
}
```

**In React (conditional rendering):**
```tsx
function Dropdown({ isOpen, children }: { isOpen: boolean; children: ReactNode }) {
  const [shouldRender, setShouldRender] = useState(isOpen);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (isOpen) setShouldRender(true);
  }, [isOpen]);

  const handleAnimationEnd = () => {
    if (!isOpen) setShouldRender(false);
  };

  if (!shouldRender) return null;

  return (
    <div
      className={isOpen ? 'dropdown-enter' : 'dropdown-exit'}
      onAnimationEnd={handleAnimationEnd}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

## 7. MODAL / DRAWER TRANSITIONS

**Backdrop:**
```css
.modal-backdrop-enter {
  animation: fadeIn var(--duration-moderate) var(--ease-out) both;
}

.modal-backdrop-exit {
  animation: fadeOut var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-in) both;
}
```

**Modal container:**
```css
.modal-enter {
  animation: scaleIn var(--duration-moderate) var(--ease-out) both;
}

.modal-exit {
  animation: fadeOut var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-in) both;
}
```

**Drawer (slide from right):**
```css
@keyframes slideInRight {
  from { transform: translateX(100%); }
  to   { transform: translateX(0); }
}

@keyframes slideOutRight {
  from { transform: translateX(0); }
  to   { transform: translateX(100%); }
}

.drawer-enter {
  animation: slideInRight var(--duration-slow) var(--ease-out) both;
}

.drawer-exit {
  animation: slideOutRight var(--duration-moderate) var(--ease-in) both;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .drawer-enter { animation: fadeIn var(--duration-moderate) var(--ease-out) both; }
  .drawer-exit  { animation: fadeOut var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-in) both; }
}
```

---

## 8. ROUTE / PAGE TRANSITIONS

Keep route transitions subtle and fast. Max `400ms`.

```css
.page-enter {
  animation: fadeSlideIn var(--duration-slow) var(--ease-out) both;
}

.page-exit {
  animation: fadeOut var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-in) both;
}
```

**With React Router / Next.js App Router:**
Wrap page content in `<FadeIn>` at the layout level. Each route's content fades in on mount.

```tsx
// Layout component
function PageLayout({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <main>
      <FadeIn duration="300ms">
        {children}
      </FadeIn>
    </main>
  );
}
```

---

## 9. TOAST / NOTIFICATION TRANSITIONS

```css
@keyframes toastSlideIn {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(16px);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}

.toast-enter {
  animation: toastSlideIn var(--duration-moderate) var(--ease-out) both;
}

.toast-exit {
  animation: fadeSlideOut var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-in) both;
}
```

---

## 10. REDUCED MOTION — NON-NEGOTIABLE

Every animated element must respect `prefers-reduced-motion`. This is an accessibility requirement.

**Strategy:** All motion-based keyframes have reduced-motion overrides defined in the global keyframes (Section 2 above). For inline transitions, use this utility:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *,
  *::before,
  *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

**Or per-component (more surgical):**
```tsx
const prefersReducedMotion =
  typeof window !== 'undefined'
    ? window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches
    : false;

const animationDuration = prefersReducedMotion ? '0ms' : '200ms';
```

---

## 11. NEVER DO

- Animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` — use `transform` instead
- Use `ease` (the CSS default) — always use the design system easing tokens
- Use `linear` timing for UI transitions (only for looping spinners/progress)
- Create animations longer than `500ms` unless it's a page-level transition
- Use `display: none` → `display: block` for show/hide — use opacity + transform
- Forget `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` on any animated element
- Add `transition` only on `:hover` — put it on the element's resting state
